issue_comments.body:
@jglick these PRs are too old to have a cached build afaict.  This:
https://jenkins.ci.cloudbees.com/job/plugins/job/github-plugin/20/

Is the oldest build available.

@jmoody 
I've added an option, which modifies the result build status if <code>GitHubCommitNotifier</code> fails to update the commit status. BTW, such approach won't help if any previous <code>Builder</code> or <code>Publisher</code> changes the status to a worse one.

Such solution resolves our case with conditional SCMs. What about yours?

@esteve 
Do you mean github-api plugin? (I guess so)
IMO it makes sense to update the dependency.

@aserrallerios 
The request should be merged into the current master branch.
Could you also add severalunit tests fro the new functionality?

@stephenc thanks for your comment, i will be glad to read some examplse/documentation of right credentials usage/implementation (or maybe i missed existed). 
1) In case of github plugin credentials: a) username+password, b) token, c) (probably) token + secure field(used for decrypting incoming hooks data) - can be reused by other GH plugins (for example i created new github-pullrequest-plugin and will be glad to fix/implement in right place credentials). 
2) Also i not really understand how URL should be matched/related/bundled in credentials. From one side GitHub related passwords are just GH related, but on other hand they can used for git https checkout communication (hm.. that also GH url related, but GH can have private installations also).

commit_comments.body:
@faulkner actually you are confusing github service and webhooks.
After my latest fix there won't be any issues if no X-Github-Event header is specified which is the case for services.

For now github has actually added the header to their service as well.

@nukulb thanks!
I think the confusion only comems from the point that this disscussion is acctually not about the cahnge in this commit anymore, but about some text which has been there before already.

I think we talk about the same things and we generally agree on the changes to be made. The only additonal thing I wanted to point out, is that in the case where a user uses the GitHub Service (instead of the plain WebHook) he has not the cance to select the encoding type - thats it. But with the alignement to the Bitbucket implementation this will not make any difference anymore.

@ndeloof 
Is there any need to increase the dependency?
We still need this plugin on 1.509 :)

@kohsuke 
Thanks for the release.
I updated the changelog on Wiki in order to reflect all changes

